headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam relied on his scoring punch, T.J. McConnell added the energy and the Indiana Pacers defense turned up the pressure in the second half Tuesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam scores 29 and fuels third-quarter charge to lead Pacers past Rockets 132-129

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving was traded away a year ago, but he's never fully left New York.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving scores 36 points in return to Brooklyn, leads Mavericks to 119-107 win over Nets

headlines.description: — It took 63 seconds for Jimmy Butler to decide the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 23, Heat used balanced attack to run past Magic 121-95

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson had 27 points and eight assists before exiting with an apparent ankle injury, Donte DiVincenzo had 32 points, and the New York Knicks hung on for a 123-113 win over the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 27 before leaving with an injury, Knicks hold on to beat Memphis 123-113

headlines.description: — Coby White and DeMar DeRozan scored 33 points apiece, and the Chicago Bulls erased a 23-point deficit in a 129-123 overtime victory over Anthony Edwards and the Minnesota Timberwolves on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White rallies the Bulls to a wild 129-123 overtime win against the Timberwolves

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 33 points and 11 rebounds to lead the Utah Jazz to a 124-117 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lauri Markkanen scores 33, leads Jazz to 124-117 win over Thunder

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant sized up the Milwaukee Bucks defense and then attacked, driving straight down the lane for a thunderous dunk over Giannis Antetokounmpo.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 32, Durant adds 28, Suns push past short-handed Bucks 114-106
